        <h2>1. Buildertrend — Best for masonry subs working with GCs</h2>
        <p>Masonry subcontractors on residential and light commercial projects benefit most from being on the same platform as their GC customers. Buildertrend dominates the residential construction space — if your GCs use it, you should know how to operate within it.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Receive and confirm task assignments from GCs</li>
          <li>Daily log submissions with in-progress photos</li>
          <li>Change order requests for extra scope (added courses, design changes)</li>
          <li>Material purchase orders tied to specific jobs</li>
          <li>Subcontractor payment applications through the system</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>Masonry subs: Buildertrend fluency makes you easier to hire. That's a real business advantage.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.buildertrend.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn">Explore Buildertrend</a>
        </div>

        <h2>2. JobTread — Best for masonry job costing</h2>
        <p>Masonry is one of the most labor-intensive trades, and productivity rates vary significantly based on bond pattern, block size, and site conditions. JobTread's real-time job costing helps you understand actual cost per unit, so you can sharpen future bids and catch overruns before they compound.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Estimate templates with material and labor line items</li>
          <li>Real-time budget vs. actual as materials arrive and labor is logged</li>
          <li>Purchase orders for block, brick, mortar, rebar — with committed cost tracking</li>
          <li>Change order workflow with margin control</li>
          <li>$99/month — accessible for masonry operations of most sizes</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>If you bid masonry work by the unit and need to know your actual cost — JobTread delivers that visibility.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.jobtread.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn btn-outline">Try JobTread</a>
        </div>

        <h2>3. Contractor Foreman — Best budget platform</h2>
        <p>Small masonry operations — a few crews, under $2M revenue — will find Contractor Foreman covers the essentials without the enterprise price tag. Estimates, time tracking, invoices, and project notes all in one platform at $49/month.</p>

        <h2>4. Procore — For commercial masonry subcontractors</h2>
        <p>Large commercial masonry subcontractors often work within Procore because their GC requires it for submittals, RFIs, and safety documentation. Procore's commercial-grade features are excellent for that environment but expensive and complex for smaller operations.</p>

        <h2>5. Houzz Pro — For decorative and residential masonry</h2>
        <p>Masonry contractors who specialize in decorative work — custom fireplaces, stone facades, hardscaping, garden walls — will find Houzz Pro's homeowner-facing marketplace valuable. Homeowners searching Houzz for masonry and stonework represent a high-intent lead pool.</p>

        <div class="cta-box">
